<!-- ── PILLARS ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="pillars-section" id="pillars">
  <div class="section-container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-label">The Framework</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">Eight Pillars of Transformation</h2>
      <p class="section-description">Each pillar addresses a distinct dimension of institutional intelligence, providing structured tools for diagnosis, development, and sustained reform.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="pillars-detail">
      <div class="pillar-row reveal">
        <div class="pillar-num">01</div>
        <div class="pillar-head"><h3>Consciousness</h3><span class="pillar-sub">Awareness &amp; Foresight</span></div>
        <div class="pillar-body"><p>Institutional consciousness refers to the collective awareness of an organization — its capacity to perceive patterns, anticipate challenges, and respond with strategic foresight. High-consciousness institutions do not merely react; they anticipate.</p><div class="pillar-apps"><div class="pillar-apps-label">Applications</div><ul><li>Strategic foresight programs</li><li>Awareness culture assessments</li><li>Institutional sensing frameworks</li></ul></div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar-row reveal">
        <div class="pillar-num">02</div>
        <div class="pillar-head"><h3>Responsibility</h3><span class="pillar-sub">Accountability &amp; Ownership</span></div>
        <div class="pillar-body"><p>Responsibility in CRIPFCnt is not compliance — it is structural placement. It asks how accountability is distributed, how performance is measured, and how individuals understand their role in the broader system they operate within.</p><div class="pillar-apps"><div class="pillar-apps-label">Applications</div><ul><li>Accountability frameworks</li><li>Performance measurement systems</li><li>Structural placement audits</li></ul></div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar-row reveal">
        <div class="pillar-num">03</div>
        <div class="pillar-head"><h3>Interpretation</h3><span class="pillar-sub">Evidence &amp; Analysis</span></div>
        <div class="pillar-body"><p>How organizations interpret evidence determines the quality of their decisions. This pillar addresses analytical frameworks, cognitive bias identification, and the design of evidence-based decision-making environments at scale.</p><div class="pillar-apps"><div class="pillar-apps-label">Applications</div><ul><li>Evidence-based decision frameworks</li><li>Bias identification programs</li><li>Analytical capacity building</li></ul></div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar-row reveal">
        <div class="pillar-num">04</div>
        <div class="pillar-head"><h3>Purpose</h3><span class="pillar-sub">Mission &amp; Alignment</span></div>
        <div class="pillar-body"><p>Purpose ensures that organizational strategy, individual motivation, and societal contribution are aligned across every level of a structure. Without clarity of purpose, institutions drift regardless of technical capability.</p><div class="pillar-apps"><div class="pillar-apps-label">Applications</div><ul><li>Mission clarity workshops</li><li>Strategic alignment programs</li><li>Purpose-led governance design</li></ul></div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar-row reveal">
        <div class="pillar-num">05</div>
        <div class="pillar-head"><h3>Frequencies</h3><span class="pillar-sub">Communication &amp; Engagement</span></div>
        <div class="pillar-body"><p>Frequencies addresses the quality and cadence of communication across institutional hierarchies. Poor communication architecture creates invisible bottlenecks — decisions that slow, information that distorts, and stakeholders that disengage.</p><div class="pillar-apps"><div class="pillar-apps-label">Applications</div><ul><li>Communication protocol design</li><li>Stakeholder engagement strategy</li><li>Information architecture audits</li></ul></div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar-row reveal">
        <div class="pillar-num">06</div>
        <div class="pillar-head"><h3>Civilization</h3><span class="pillar-sub">Society &amp; Infrastructure</span></div>
        <div class="pillar-body"><p>Civilization asks how institutions contribute to, or detract from, the societies they inhabit. It provides frameworks for sustainable development, public accountability, and the long-term stewardship of civic infrastructure.</p><div class="pillar-apps"><div class="pillar-apps-label">Applications</div><ul><li>Public accountability frameworks</li><li>Sustainable development programs</li><li>Civic infrastructure planning</li></ul></div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar-row reveal">
        <div class="pillar-num">07</div>
        <div class="pillar-head"><h3>Negotiation</h3><span class="pillar-sub">Dialogue &amp; Consensus</span></div>
        <div class="pillar-body"><p>In multi-stakeholder environments, the quality of negotiation — not the strength of any single party — determines outcomes. This pillar develops strategic dialogue competencies, consensus methodologies, and conflict transformation tools.</p><div class="pillar-apps"><div class="pillar-apps-label">Applications</div><ul><li>Strategic dialogue training</li><li>Consensus-building methodology</li><li>Multi-stakeholder facilitation</li></ul></div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar-row reveal">
        <div class="pillar-num">08</div>
        <div class="pillar-head"><h3>Technology</h3><span class="pillar-sub">AI &amp; Digital Transformation</span></div>
        <div class="pillar-body"><p>Technology is understood not merely as infrastructure but as a strategic enabler of institutional transformation. This pillar covers AI integration, data governance, digital service delivery, and technology-enabled accountability systems.</p><div class="pillar-apps"><div class="pillar-apps-label">Applications</div><ul><li>Digital transformation strategy</li><li>AI integration frameworks</li><li>Data governance systems</li></ul></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

